- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on the application of model predictive controllers to robotic manipulators, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of control theory and optimization techniques to design and implement the controllers, which is a key aspect of systems and control. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, the use of predictive models and optimization techniques can be seen as a form of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Similar to the previous point, the use of predictive models and optimization techniques can be seen as a form of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not directly relate to computer vision, robotic manipulators often rely on vision systems for sensing and perception, which could be relevant to this sub-category.
